		<div class="lia-message-body-content">
			
                
                    <P><FONT face="times new roman,times" size="3">Chapter 15: In the Asteroid Field Part 3</FONT></P><P><FONT face="times new roman,times" size="3">&nbsp;</FONT></P><P><FONT face="times new roman,times" size="3">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Shadow immediately looked over his shoulder at the source of the attacks, which had momentarily stopped. On a chunk from which they were going farther and farther, he noticed two laser blasters aiming at them. He did not know whether they were robotic or controlled by someone who was somewhere else, but he knew that they then started firing him. Shadow maneuvered to avoid the fire, but he also had to dodge the floating rocks, so he was hit by some lasers. Soon more guns installed at other asteroids located them. Now, Shadow did not wonder why so many explorers had been lost in these places. Someone had made sure they wouldn’t survive. All three of them tried to stay as intact as possible, but they would often either get hit or bump on the chunks. They, especially Magical, were also attacking the blasters, but it was difficult to hit them. Magical smashed the small asteroids, so that they could pass more easily, too.</FONT></P><P><FONT face="times new roman,times" size="3">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; And as if that wasn’t enough suddenly, two other rockets appeared behind them. And it seemed that the ones on them were not friendly. Trying to fight back, Magical managed to hit the one rocket sometimes making its pilot lose control, while Shadow finally managed to build something. It was only a brick wall, but Shadow released and it suddenly floated in space in front of the other rocket. It crashed on it and it stayed behind.</FONT></P>
                
            
			
