                    <P><FONT face="times new roman,times" size="3">Chapter 15: In the Asteroid Field Part 4<BR /></FONT></P><P><FONT face="times new roman,times" size="3">&nbsp;</FONT></P><P><FONT face="times new roman,times" size="3">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; By that time, their rockets were getting serious damage. Yet, as if miraculously they suddenly got out of the Field. They had reached the other end!</FONT></P><P><FONT face="times new roman,times" size="3">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; It seemed too easy to Shadow. Certainly, it was very dangerous, but not enough for everyone to be lost. And then it hit him! What if some of them did get past? What if the real danger lay after the Asteroid Field?</FONT></P><P><FONT face="times new roman,times" size="3">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; They kept going for a while. The rocketeers did not appear again. Then, they noticed a world near them.</FONT></P><P><FONT face="times new roman,times" size="3">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “Let’s go there!” he said to his comm..</FONT></P><P><FONT face="times new roman,times" size="3">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Shadow put aside his fears. Whoever and whatever they were facing they had made a mistake. They had made it personal. . .</FONT></P><P>&nbsp;</P><P><FONT face="times new roman,times" size="3">Bewαre of the shαdows becαuse I might be there.</FONT></P>
                
            
			
