		<div class="lia-message-body lia-component-body" id="messagebodydisplay_0_3" class="lia-message-body">
	
		<div class="lia-message-body-content">
			
                
                    <BLOCKQUOTE><HR />fffffplayer1 wrote:<BR /><P><FONT face="times new roman,times" size="3">Chapter 15: In the Asteroid Field Part 2<BR /></FONT></P><P><FONT face="times new roman,times" size="3">&nbsp;</FONT></P><P><FONT face="times new roman,times" size="3">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Kate had known she couldn’t change his mind and so she didn’t try. Shadow was very mulish some –or many– times.</FONT></P><P><FONT face="times new roman,times" size="3">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Now, the three of the four original FFFFF members were piloting their rockets to save the fourth. Despite Shadow’s worries, part of him felt pleased that it was them working together again. They often got separated nowadays.</FONT></P><P><FONT face="times new roman,times" size="3">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Zephyr Asteroid Field did not consist of actual asteroids. They were just chunks of Crux that did not come from the surface. They varied in size and shape, but what they all had in common was that there was no life on them and that there was no level surface on them. The field had a spherical shape and had about the same diameter as the Nimbus System, but theoretically there could be something inside it. That was what they were going to find out today.</FONT></P><P><FONT face="times new roman,times" size="3">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In the beginning, they were just flying their rockets maneuvering to avoid the chunks. However, about half an hour after they entered the field, something started firing them. The first hits, the ones that surprised them, were on Kate’s rocket. Luckily, Shadow, in knowledge of the danger of the Field, despite not knowing its origin, had prepared by strengthening the rockets’ shields and weapons. Even so, Kate’s rocket was slightly damaged and it almost hit an asteroid.</FONT></P><HR /></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Mulish, that's a fun word.<img class="emoticon emoticon-thinking" id="thinking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/thinking.png" alt="Thinking" title="Thinking" /><img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /> Great chapter!<img class="emoticon emoticon-happy" id="happy" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/happy.png" alt="Happy" title="Happy" /></P>
                
            
			
