		<div class="lia-message-body lia-component-body" id="messagebodydisplay_0_4" class="lia-message-body">
	
		<div class="lia-message-body-content">
			
                
                    <P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">Chapter 16: The Investigation Begins Part 1<BR /></FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Three rockets landed on the first world one would meet if they passed the Zephyr Asteroid Field coming from Avant Gardens’ direction. Shadow, Kate and Magical got off of them and examined their surroundings.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; They were in a world that seemed kind of empty, deserted. It was a level surface continuing for many kilometres in all directions but for behind since they’d come that way. This land of brown soil was empty of plants, people, houses, sounds… life! Only on the background far ahead of them there were some mountains. The place seemed vast, but it was an effect partially created by the emptiness since it was actually smaller than other worlds like Crux Prime.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “Doesn’t seem very lively, does it?” Shadow commented.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “Perhaps there could be something at the other side where the mountains are!” Kate replied.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “We should check! I don’t think there’s anything anywhere else, if there even is something at the mountains!” Shadow agreed.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The got in their rockets again and flew to the other side. However, after long investigation by the mountains and over the mountains they found nothing. The mountains were the end of the world, so there was no need to search behind them.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The minifigures left slightly disappointed, but there was still hope. The area inside the Asteroid Field would be quite large, if the width of the asteroid field was the same throughout the whole of its. That would leave much space for many worlds hiding many secrets.</FONT></P><P>&nbsp;</P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">---</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">Wow! It's been some time since I last wrote! *face palm*</FONT></P>
                
            
			
				<div style="width:98%; max-height:100px; overflow:hidden;" class="UserSignature lia-message-signature">
