		<div class="lia-message-body-content">
			
                
                    <P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">Chapter 16: The Investigation Begins Part 2<BR /></FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Indeed it wasn’t long before they reached another world. Its shape revealed from afar that it must have belonged to a mountain range before the explosion of Crux. And as they got closer, it was revealed that the particular mountains at least were not just any mountains. They were volcanoes. The red lava was visible due to its brightness and it seemed to be everywhere in the world.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Soon, they descended and landed in a point that seemed to be safer than others. This world, contrary to the other was busy with people. They were going about to their business and some didn’t even notice them. Some held mattocks or other tools of the like. There were some vehicles that seemed to be purposed for mining. The people probably were miners.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; One of them approached scanned each of them from head to toe and then talked.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “Ye’re no from these parts, are ye? Ye do looks quite strangers!” he told them.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “Indeed we don’t come from here! We’re of the Nexus Force!” Shadow replied.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “Well, then! Welcome teh the Magma Tops!” the other one said “Now, ye must leave! Goodbye!”. . .</FONT></P>
                
            
			
