		<div class="lia-message-body lia-component-body" id="messagebodydisplay_0_6" class="lia-message-body">
	
		<div class="lia-message-body-content">
			
                
                    <P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">Chapter 17: At the Magma Tops Part 1<BR /></FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “What? Why must we leave?” Kate exclaimed confused.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “Ye are not welcome here! They don’t likes the lot af ye!” the miner explained a bit more.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “What lot do you mean the lot of us?” Magical requested seeming offended or ready to be.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “The Nexus-Forcers! They don’t likes them! They wills pursue ye! Ye should leave now!”</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “You mind if you share your name with us, my fellow?” Shadow asked for his name.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “I am Barber!”</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “And who would <EM>they </EM>be?”</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “The Ensee, the ones who has forced us teh mine for them! Magma Tops used teh be a happiest place where people mined for their living, but also enjoyed it. We even had a truce with the Rocks! But then they and the Maelstrom came. The Maelstrom caused trouble, but they… they came with guns and threatened us and forced us the work for them. They brought more miners and they are tyrannical!”</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; It was at that moment that Shadow noticed that other than the miners there were also some minifigures with rifles wearing slightly different clothes. They were watching around to make sure that everyone did what they should be doing. Two of them were looking their direction. They didn’t seem very friendly. All of this was bad news. This threat they were facing seemed to become bigger and bigger. And it created Shadow a feeling that he was slowly being pressed from all sides.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Another miner approached them.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “Barber, they want ye with something!” he said and pointed to the guards looking at them.</FONT></P>
                
            
			
