		<div class="lia-message-body-content">
			
                
                    <P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">Chapter 17: At the Magma Tops Part 3</FONT></P><P>&nbsp;</P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Yet, he did react when the little part of his brain that still paid attention to what was happening around notified him that his wife and friend were in danger. Their pursuers seemed to have stopped at some point, but Shadow did not remember when. It was Maelstrom that was attacking them. They looked like the rock monsters from the Power Miners genre. However, they were infected and some instead of crystal parts had magma parts. Most of them were of the small kind, but there were also two of the big troll-like ones, one magma and one crystal. There were also good old Stromlings and some creatures that looked like infected magma-rock minifigures. They outnumbered them by far.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; They were outside the aforementioned cave in a rock plateau next to which there was some sort of lava river stemming from an opening to the wall and entering another cave in which there was some rock space where one could walk, a little like a sidewalk. They were underground and in fact it all was just a bigger cave. It was really really hot.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Shadow got his ice saw and shield. He figured arrows wouldn’t be of any use against the rock monsters. One Crystalling approached him and he attacked it with the ice saw, but it did not seem to be very hurt. Shadow hit again and afterwards was punched. The crystal hand of the creature on his stomach hurt quite much. He couldn’t resist bending and the creature punched him again this time managing to reach his nose due to his having bent down. Another of them approached, but this one of the Magma kind. He felt the heat rise next to him. Another punch brought him on the ground, while the Magmaling ignited his cape with its touch.</FONT></P>
                
            
			
