                    <P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">Chapter 17: At the Magma Tops Part 4</FONT></P><P>&nbsp;</P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A sword was brought down upon the Magmaling with great force smashing it to pieces. Luckily, the magma of the creatures was not really of the same nature with the actual magma, so the burns at the spots where it hit Shadow were not that awful. Magical, for it was to him, that the sword belonged smashed the Crystalling, too.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “You’ll have to do better than that!” he commented while he picked Shadow up after he had extinguished the flames.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A rock smashed just above the head of Magical. It was the Crystal Troll that was throwing rocks at them. They ran to avoid them and bumped to some Stromling, which fell more easily than the other creatures. As they continued to dodge rocks, they did the unfortunate thing to stumble upon the Magma Troll. It looked at them for a second, confused, and then roared. They could see the brightness of hot interior of its mouth. And then lava came out of it. Shadow was quick to put his shield between him and the terrible heat of the liquid. He was indeed protected, but was not as happy due to the fact his shield and part of his fake hand had been melted down.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “Brick it!” he exclaimed and grabbed a Big One.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Meanwhile, Kate had found her weapons useless, too, and was using some dynamites. They were indeed effective and could smash many of them together. The only problem was she did not have an infinite amount of them. She grabbed the last bundle of three and considered what would be its best use. She resolved it would be on the Crystal Troll and when it opened its mouth to roar once more, she shoved it inside. The Troll exploded in many rock and crystal pieces.</FONT></P>
                
            
			
