		<div class="lia-message-body lia-component-body" id="messagebodydisplay_0_10" class="lia-message-body">
	
		<div class="lia-message-body-content">
			
                
                    <P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">Chapter 17: At the Magma Tops Part 5</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Despite some momentary successes though, they didn’t seem to have many chances to keep fighting for long. There was still the Magma Troll and many Magmalings and Crystallings. Magical was the only one to seem to have some success, but even he could not help it with the Magma Troll, which did not get smashed even with explosives. The other two tried to find a weapon with which they’d smash more of them and tried not to get beaten too much.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; And then sounded some drums and a horn. They all, the Maelstrom included, looked above them from where the sounds had come before they started echoing all around the cave’s chamber. And as they still looked a large rock fell and hit the Magma Troll smashing it to pieces. In no time, the plateau was swarmed by rock creatures, magma and crystal, coming from both entrances, from above and even with a rock boat from the lava river. They were not infected, though. They started fighting the Maelstrom Rocklings and the Stromlings. They were more and soon defeated the Maelstrom.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Once that had been achieved they turned their attention to the three minifigures. They created a circle around them and some of them talked to each other with hoarse voices that would be the natural voices for stones, if they had voices. Yet, they spoke a language they did not understand, weird and very different from the one they talked. Out of the mass of rock creatures, came a Magma one that was quite big compared to the rest and was holding a scepter of stone at the top of which there was a crystal of colour orange. He must have been some sort of leader. Once he arrived everyone hushed.</FONT></P>
                
            
			
				<div style="width:98%; max-height:100px; overflow:hidden;" class="UserSignature lia-message-signature">
