		<div class="lia-message-body lia-component-body" id="messagebodydisplay_0_11" class="lia-message-body">
	
		<div class="lia-message-body-content">
			
                
                    <P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">Chapter 17: At the Magma Tops Part 6<BR /></FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He talked to them, but they didn’t understand. Yet, his feelings were obvious due to his somewhat angry tone and his threatening pointing of his staff.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “We are very grateful for saving us! However, I regret to tell you that I do not understand your language and I fear you might not understand mine. However, I would like to point out, just in case, that we come in peace and do not wish for any trouble!” Shadow said with a hope that this might make things better.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The leader said something to another Magma creature and the other replied something. They seemed to agree. There were some whispers from the crowd. Suddenly, the leader shouted something and the crowd opened up. Three of them approached each of them and together they started carrying them towards the lava.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “Shadow, what are these?” Magical asked with obvious worry.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “I assume they are the Rocks Barber mentioned!” Shadow answered and the remembrance of Barber was a pain.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “Are they going to throw us in the lava?” Magical continued.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; “I haven’t the slightest idea!” Shadow responded with a calmness that surprised even himself.</FONT></P><P><FONT size="3" face="times new roman,times">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; But it turned out the strange creatures had no such intentions –for now at least. They placed them in the rock boat and after some rock creatures, the leader included boarded it, too, it was set to move freely down the river. Their destination? Unknown. . .</FONT></P>
                
            
			
				<div style="width:98%; max-height:100px; overflow:hidden;" class="UserSignature lia-message-signature">
